channel.title: Error Message, SOMEBODY HELP!
channel.description:
I really wanted to get back into moparscape, as i used to play and loved it! i keep getting the following message when trying to log in:
Error: T2 - 126,126,126 - 13,3038,3356 - 80,111,105,110,116,115,58,32,48,32,10,76,-59,
It logs me in, but logs it straight back out again!
SOMEBODY PLEASE HELP!

item.title: Error Message, SOMEBODY HELP!
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

The error seems to be the message that you’re sending.

Error: T2 - lastPacket,second,third - length,playerX,playerY - data

So in your case, you sent packet 126 3 times, the last one had a size of 13 bytes, you were standing at (3038, 3356), and the data was:

80,111,105,110,116,115,58,32,48,32,10,76,-59,

which translates into hex results in

which translates into the ASCII string

Points: 0\nL-

The problem could be that the end of the string (\n, 10, or 0A) was reached while there was still data remaining.

Read full topic
